svg:svg.svg:text: Two enclosures are shown here as bolded boxes. Each contains a margin shown here in pink.
Inner content is to be placed within the margins.
The nested enclosure has position specified by:
to position it at offset 1 to the containing enclosure and width w=2.
Enclosures also define an outer area to hold content like link attachments and their labels.
The outer area is defined by attributes wl wr ht and hb.
Outer content has padding shown here in yellow.
The nested enclosure here has padding=0.1, margin=0.2, wl=0.9, wr=0.9
Overall x extent of box = 2 * padding + wl + w + wr = 4
